Daniel HOGAN, Appellant, v. Henry C. HILL, Warden, etc. No. 5778. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. July 16, 1935. ( Abram M. Frumbcrg, of New York City, and Andrew A. Leiser, of Lewis-burg, Pa. (I. Reines Skier and Jacob F. Adelman, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Frank J. McDonnell, U. S. Atty., of Scranton, Pa., Herman F. Reich, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Sunbury, Pa., and A. E. Gottshall, of Washington, D. C., for appellee.

Before BUFFINGTON, DAVIS, and THOMPSON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

After hearing and due consideration, we find no error committed by the hearing judge. So holding, his order dismissing the petition is affirmed.
